Gauteng residents were shocked by a 2.7 magnitude tremor on Sunday, 27 February.The tremor that was felt by residents of Centurion and Midrand, Johannesburg was recorded around 1:29 pm.The size of the tremor was shared by a forecast Twitter page, Gauteng Weather.“Breaking: 2.7-magnitude tremor with epicentre near Centurion recorded at 13:29 on Sunday!!!”This is the third tremor in a matter of a four months. Last month, on 18 January, a tremor measuring 3.5 on the local magnitude scale was recorded in Westonaria, southwest of Johannesburg.In October 2021, another tremor of the same magnitude of 3.5 was felt around Ekurhuleni and the epicentre was Boksburg, Ekurhuleni around 06:32 am.Reacting to Sunday’s tremor in Centurion, people shared their experiences. Others were asking if there was really a tremor or they only felt it by themselves.Screenwriter, Phathutshedzo Makwarela asked if everyone felt the tremor.“So all of us in Centurion felt the tremor?” he asked.TheMqhele also asked: “Haibo am I the only who just felt a tremor in Centurion?”Another user, AlucZ tweeted: “Hope that was just a tremor and not an earthquake. Centurion just shook and there was also a bang. Must be blasting at that concrete mine operation going on here.”  ?? BREAKING: 2.7-MAGNITUDE TREMOR WITH EPICENTRE NEAR CENTURION RECORDED AT 13:29 ON SUNDAY!!!  So all of us in Centurion felt the tremor ???? Haibo am I the only who just felt a tremor in Centurion? Hope that was just a tremor and not an earthquake. Centurion just shook and there was also a bang. Must be blasting at that concrete mine operation going on here.   